OSCE envoy - West ' s troops must stay in Bosnia . Europe ' s security envoy to Bosnia called on Saturday for a Western peacekeeping presence to remain in the divided country for the " indefinite future " to deal with a potentially explosive situation . " The international community has to stay there for years to help stabilise the situation . Both civil and the military need to commit for the indefinite future . We have to commit to a significant number , " Robert Frowick , head of the Organisation for Security and Cooperation in Europe ( OSCE ) mission to Bosnia , told a news conference . The NATO - led peace force is due to leave Bosnia in June 1998 . 
